The paper discusses the impact of blockage and antenna directivity on the performance of a millimeter-wave personal network, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of millimeter-wave communications is also a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper considers the effects of correlated blocking, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
